    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Bed Murphy's Law Can't Touch</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Frances Anderton</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Photo of updated Murphy bed designed by Vico Magistretti (Currents: Los Angeles)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An update on the Murphy bed: the Vanja Container bed, by the Italian designer Vico Magistretti, is aimed at apartment dwellers who want style and storage space. The Vanja Container is an ingenious marriage of a Shaker-style cherry-wood base and headboard and a high-tech lifting device derived from Mercedes automobile mechanics. The bed (priced at a king-size $3,200) was introduced at the Milan furniture fair this year, and is available at Dormire, 1345 Fourth Street in Santa Monica, (310) 393-9288.</p>
      </block>
